
                                            The incident took place after officers were alerted to be on the lookout for a hijacked car.
                                         CAPE TOWN - A suspected car hijacker has been wounded in a gun battle with police in Manenberg.  Over the weekend, officers had pulled over a vehicle the man was driving in after being alerted to be on the lookout for a hijacked car. Two occupants tried to flee the scene. One of them opened fire on police who retaliated, wounding one of them. Nine suspects were eventually taken into custody. (Edited by Shimoney Regter)